    "answer_id" : 69267377,
    "question_id" : 16602017,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>mvn package command will compile source code and also package it as a jar or war as per pom file and put it into the target folder(by default).</p>\n<p>mvn install command will compile and package, but it will also put the package in your local repository. So that other projects can refer to it and grab it from your local repository.</p>\n<p>mvn install command is mostly used when you wants to compile a project(library) which other projects in your repository are depending on.</p>\n"
  } ],
